definitions.definition: Either of two species of rattlesnake having a diamond pattern on the back: Crotalus adamanteus , found in the southeastern United States, and Crotalus atrox , found in the southwestern United States and northwestern and central Mexico .
The saltmarsh terrapin of the Atlantic coast ( Malaclemys terrapin ).

main_definition: ( common name ) Either of two species of rattlesnake having a diamond pattern on the back: Crotalus adamanteus , found in the southeastern United States, and Crotalus atrox , found in the southwestern United States and northwestern and central Mexico .
